[SkillPath "declarer_play/squeeze_plays"]
[Student "S"]
{North is to play 7NT. East leads the \SQ.

One more winner is needed. Dummy's fourth \C is a possibility.

So take the \SK and play \C A K Q.

East discards a \S on the third \C. 

Now you know West guards the \Cs.

Before tackling \Ds, see what you can discover about \Ss.

Play the \SA. West discards a \H. 

West guards the \Cs. East guards the \Ss. Nobody can guard the \Hs.

Play 4 rounds of \Ds. 

[showcards N:S9,H6,D4,C8 E:HQ,H9,H8,CJ S:S7,HA,HK,H5 W:SJ,HJ,HT,H7]

On the fourth \D West had to discard a \H. You discarded a small \S. East discarded a \S on the third \D and a \H on the fourth.

Play dummy's \D4. West cannot throw the \CJ or he will set up dummy's \C8, so he discards a \H.

You discard the \S7.

Now East is squeezed. He cannot discard the \SJ or he will set up dummy's \S9, so he discards a \H.

You win the last three \H tricks with another Double Squeeze.}
[Play "W"]SQ

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "E:5.AKJ983.A5.K863 AKJ94.64.T72.QT2 T873.QT.KQ6.A975 Q62.752.J9843.J4"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "6H"]
